BabyLeap Privacy Policy
Last Updated: November 19, 2024
Welcome to BabyLeap!
Our Services enable parents and guardians to store, share, preserve, and organize information and media about their children's lives, including personal information. We take the privacy and security of personal information very seriously. This Privacy Policy outlines how BabyLeap (referred to as "we, " "us, " or "our ") collects and uses personal information through our apps, websites, and services related to the BabyLeap products and services (collectively, the "Services "). 

Please review this Privacy Policy carefully. By accessing or using the Services, you agree to this Privacy Policy and consent to the use of your personal information (including personal information about others that you provide to us) as outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you disagree with any provisions of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use the Services and contact us to correct, amend, or delete any collected personal information. If you have any questions about our privacy practices or your rights regarding personal information, please contact us at hello@babyleap.app. You can also reach us at the following address: Omega Solutions, MB, V. Nageviciaus g. 3, Vilnius, Lithuania
Applicability of this Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy applies solely to personal information collected through the Services. We process personal information based on legal grounds, including your consent, contractual obligations, and legitimate interests. This Privacy Policy does not apply to anonymous information or third-party websites or services linked to the Services ( "Third Party Linked Sites "). We are not responsible for the privacy or data security practices of Third Party Linked Sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.
Collection and Use of Personal Information
Account Information – We collect the following personal information you provide directly or indirectly ( "Account Information "): Contact information: name, email address, mailing address, phone number. Billing information: credit card number, billing address. Preferences information: product/content interests, communication/marketing preferences. Usage activity: purchase history, viewed content, site areas visited. Demographic information: age, education, gender, interests, zip code. We may collect information from third parties (e.g., when others provide your information to invite you to use the Services), data enrichment services (to tailor communications), or when you link your Account to third-party services.
Device Information – We automatically collect information about your device and Services usage ( "Device Information "), such as IP address, browser type, pages, and operating system. We use Account Information and Device Information for: Creating and administering your Account. Providing Services. Improving and customizing Services. Monitoring Service performance and usage. Understanding user acquisition sources. Processing orders/requests. Providing customer support. Sending communications. Linking Accounts with third-party services. Securing Services. Sharing with third parties (see "Disclosure to Third Parties ").
User Content – Personal information included in User Content (e.g., photos, videos) may be collected for Service-related purposes. User Content is used to provide Services, ensure stability, improve algorithms, and respond to inquiries. Disclosure to Third Parties We share personal information with third parties in these cases: With your consent. With vendors providing Services aspects. With vendors for business analytics/insights. As required by law. In corporate events (e.g., merger). Access and Control of Your Personal Information You can access, correct, amend, or delete User Content and Account Information. You control User Content.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies (and How to Opt Out)
We use tracking technologies to gather Device Information. You can change settings to disable tracking technologies, but note this may render Services unusable. Children Parents/guardians can upload children's information, but we do not knowingly collect info from anyone under 13. Services are not intended for users under 13. Security We implement safeguards to protect personal information. For details, contact us. International Transfers We process/store info in the US and other countries. By using Services, you consent to such transfers. Changes to Privacy Policy We may update this Privacy Policy. Material changes will be communicated via email and posted on our website. Questions? Contact us at hello@babyleap.app.
Consent to Share Consumption Data with Apple:
By using our app and making in-app purchases, you consent to our sharing of data regarding your usage and consumption of purchased content with Apple, as part of our efforts to resolve refund requests. This information may include details about how you have accessed and interacted with the purchased content. The purpose of sharing this data is to help Apple make an informed decision regarding refund requests. We ensure that such data sharing is done in compliance with Apple's policies and only as necessary to process your requests.